results.name: Number of free pure symmetric multifunctions with one atom, n positions, and no empty or unitary parts (subexpressions of the form x[] or x[y]).
comment: Also the number of orderless Mathematica expressions with one atom, n positions, and no empty or unitary parts.
link: Andrew Howroyd, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..200
program: seq(n)={my(v=[1]); for(n=2, n, my(t=EulerT(v)-v); v=concat(v, sum(k=1, n-2, v[k]*t[n-k-1]))); v} \\ _Andrew Howroyd_, Aug 19 2018
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Aug 15 2018
ext: Terms a(29) and beyond from _Andrew Howroyd_, Aug 19 2018
